entity.name: Steve Yegge
entity.text: Steve Yegge is an American software engineer, engineering leader, and technology blogger known for his candid and influential writings on programming languages, developer productivity, software engineering practices, and industry culture over two decades. Yegge began his career in the early 1990s at GeoWorks, a software company focused on operating systems and applications for personal computers. From 1998 to 2005, he served as a Senior Manager of Software Development at Amazon, where he [...] Steve Yegge began his professional career in 1992 at GeoWorks, a software company developing graphical operating systems for early personal computers. As a software engineer, he focused on building developer tools to support the maintenance and extension of the company's flagship product, GEOS, a 16-bit graphical operating system targeted at 8086 processors. His role involved working with millions of lines of 8086 assembly code that formed the core of GEOS and its associated applications, [...] company, as an engineering leader focused on platform development. After a brief retirement, he returned to the industry in October 2022 as Head of Engineering at Sourcegraph, where he leads efforts to advance AI-powered developer tools, including the Cody AI coding assistant and the open-source SCIP protocol for code intelligence. Over his 30-plus-year career, Yegge has written over one million lines of production code across 12 programming languages and alternated between individual
